{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781051178601,"sessionID":"ses_1511b64a7ffevvFJkOHaY5EHeu","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_m00y22v6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"converters.py","content":"b'def celsius_to_fahrenheit(celsius):\\n    \"\"\"Convert Celsius to Fahrenheit.\\\"\\n    if not isinstance(celsius, (int, float)):\\n        raise TypeError(\"Input must be a numeric value.\")\\n    return (celsius * 9/5) + 32\\n\\ndef fahrenheit_to_celsius(fahrenheit):\\n    \"\"\"Convert Fahrenheit to Celsius.\\\"\\n    if not isinstance(fahrenheit, (int, float)):\\n        raise TypeError(\"Input must be a numeric value.\")\\n    return (fahrenheit - 32) * 5/9\\n\\ndef celsius_to_kelvin(celsius):\\n    \"\"\"Convert Celsius to Kelvin.\\\"\\n    if not isinstance(celsius, (int, float)):\\n        raise TypeError(\"Input must be a numeric value.\")\\n    return celsius + 273.15'\n\nb'import pytest\\nfrom converters import celsius_to_fahrenheit, fahrenheit_to_celsius, celsius_to_kelvin\\n\\ndef test_celsius_to_fahrenheit():\\n    assert celsius_to_fahrenheit(0) == 32.0\\n    assert celsius_to_fahrenheit(100) == 212.0\\n    assert celsius_to_fahrenheit(25) == 77.0\\n    with pytest.raises(TypeError):\\n        celsius_to_fahrenheit(\"string\")\\n    with pytest.raises(TypeError):\\n        celsius_to_fahrenheit(None)\\n\\ndef test_fahrenheit_to_celsius():\\n    assert fahrenheit_to_celsius(32) == 0.0\\n    assert fahrenheit_to_celsius(212) == 100.0\\n    assert fahrenheit_to_celsius(77) == 25.0\\n    with pytest.raises(TypeError):\\n        fahrenheit_to_celsius(\"string\")\\n    with pytest.raises(TypeError):\\n        fahrenheit_to_celsius(None)\\n\\ndef test_celsius_to_kelvin():\\n    assert celsius_to_kelvin(0) == 273.15\\n    assert celsius_to_kelvin(-273.15) == 0.0\\n    assert celsius_to_kelvin(100) == 373.15\\n    with pytest.raises(TypeError):\\n        celsius_to_kelvin(\"string\")\\n    with pytest.raises(TypeError):\\n        celsius_to_kelvin(None)'\n\nb'import argparse\\nfrom converters import celsius_to_fahrenheit, fahrenheit_to_celsius, celsius_to_kelvin\\n\\ndef main():\\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\\'Convert temperature units.\\')\\n    parser.add_argument(\\'temperature\\', type=float, help=\\'Temperature value to convert.\\')\\n    parser.add_argument(\\'--from\\',\\'-f\\', required=True, choices=[\\'celsius\\', \\'fahrenheit\\', \\'kelvin\\'], help=\\'Source unit (celsius, fahrenheit, kelvin).\\')\\n    parser.add_argument(\\'--to\\',\\'-t\\', required=True, choices=[\\'celsius\\', \\'fahrenheit\\', \\'kelvin\\'], help=\\'Target unit (celsius, fahrenheit, kelvin).\\')\\n    args = parser.parse_args()\\n\\n    if args.from == \\'celsius\\' and args.to == \\'fahrenheit\\':\\n        result = celsius_to_fahrenheit(args.temperature)\\n    elif args.from == \\'fahrenheit\\' and args.to == \\'celsius\\':\\n        result = fahrenheit_to_celsius(args.temperature)\\n    elif args.from == \\'celsius\\' and args.to == \\'kelvin\\':\\n        result = celsius_to_kelvin(args.temperature)\\n    else:\\n        parser.error(f\"Conversion from {args.from} to {args.to} is not supported. Supported conversions: Celsius→Fahrenheit, Fahrenheit→Celsius, Celsius→Kelvin\")\\n\\n    print(f\"{args.temperature} {args.from} is equal to {result} {args.to}.\")\\n\\nif __name__ == \\'__main__\\':\\n    main()'\n\nb'import pytest\\nimport sys\\nfrom cli import main\\n\\ndef test_celsius_to_fahrenheit(monkeypatch):\\n    monkeypatch.setattr(sys, \"argv\", [\"script.py\", \"--temperature\", \"25\", \"--from\", \"celsius\", \"--to\", \"fahrenheit\"])\\n    with pytest.capture_output() as cap:\\n        main()\\n    assert cap.stdout == \"25 celsius is equal to 77.0 fahrenheit.\\\\n\"\\n\\ndef test_fahrenheit_to_celsius(monkeypatch):\\n    monkeypatch.setattr(sys, \"argv\", [\"script.py\", \"--temperature\", \"77\", \"--from\", \"fahrenheit\", \"--to\", \"celsius\"])\\n    with pytest.capture_output() as cap:\\n        main()\\n    assert cap.stdout == \"77 fahrenheit is equal to 25.0 celsius.\\\\n\"\\n\\ndef test_celsius_to_kelvin(monkeypatch):\\n    monkeypatch.setattr(sys, \"argv\", [\"script.py\", \"--temperature\", \"0\", \"--from\", \"celsius\", \"--to\", \"kelvin\"])\\n    with pytest.capture_output() as cap:\\n        main()\\n    assert cap.stdout == \"0 celsius is equal to 273.15 kelvin.\\\\n\"\\n\\ndef test_unsupported_conversion(monkeypatch):\\n    monkeypatch.setattr(sys, \"argv\", [\"script.py\", \"--temperature\", \"100\", \"--from\", \"fahrenheit\", \"--to\", \"kelvin\"])\\n    with pytest.raises(SystemExit) as excinfo:\\n        main()\\n    assert \"Conversion from fahrenheit to kelvin is not supported\" in str(excinfo.value)\\n\\ndef test_missing_temperature(monkeypatch):\\n    monkeypatch.setattr(sys, \"argv\", [\"script.py\", \"--from\", \"celsius\", \"--to\", \"fahrenheit\"])\\n    with pytest.raises(SystemExit) as excinfo:\\n        main()\\n    assert \"the following arguments are required: temperature\" in str(excinfo.value)\\n\\ndef test_missing_from(monkeypatch):\\n    monkeypatch.setattr(sys, \"argv\", [\"script.py\", \"--temperature\", \"100\", \"--to\", \"fahrenheit\"])\\n    with pytest.raises(SystemExit) as excinfo:\\n        main()\\n    assert \"the following arguments are required: --from\" in str(excinfo.value)\\n\\ndef test_missing_to(monkeypatch):\\n    monkeypatch.setattr(sys, \"argv\", [\"script.py\", \"--temperature\", \"100\", \"--from\", \"celsius\"])\\n    with pytest.raises(SystemExit) as excinfo:\\n        main()\\n    assert \"the following arguments are required: --to\" in str(excinfo.value)\\n\\ndef test_invalid_from_unit(monkeypatch):\\n    monkeypatch.setattr(sys, \"argv\", [\"script.py\", \"--temperature\", \"100\", \"--from\", \"invalid\", \"--to\", \"fahrenheit\"])\\n    with pytest.raises(SystemExit) as excinfo:\\n        main()\\n    assert \"invalid choice: invalid (choose from celsius, fahrenheit, kelvin)\" in str(excinfo.value)\\n\\ndef test_invalid_to_unit(monkeypatch):\\n    monkeypatch.setattr(sys, \"argv\", [\"script.py\", \"--temperature\", \"100\", \"--from\", \"celsius\", \"--to\", \"invalid\"])\\n    with pytest.raises(SystemExit) as excinfo:\\n        main()\\n    assert \"invalid choice: invalid (choose from celsius, fahrenheit, kelvin)\" in str(excinfo.value)'\n\nb'# temperature-conversion-library\\n\\nA simple library for converting temperature units between Celsius, Fahrenheit, and Kelvin.\\n\\n## Installation\\n\\nInstall the package using pip:\\n\\n```bash\\npip install .\\n```\\n\\n## Usage\\n\\n### As a Python library\\n\\nImport and use the conversion functions:\\n\\n```python\\nfrom converters import celsius_to_fahrenheit, fahrenheit_to_celsius, celsius_to_kelvin\\n\\n# Example\\nfahrenheit = celsius_to_fahrenheit(25)\\ncelsius = fahrenheit_to_celsius(77)\\nkelvin = celsius_to_kelvin(0)\\n```\\n\\n### As a CLI tool\\n\\nUse the command-line interface to convert temperatures:\\n\\n```bash\\npython cli.py --temperature <value> --from <unit> --to <unit>\\n```\\n\\n**Supported units**: `celsius`, `fahrenheit`, `kelvin`  \\n**Supported conversions**:\\n- Celsius → Fahrenheit\\n- Fahrenheit → Celsius\\n- Celsius → Kelvin\\n\\n**Example**:\\n```bash\\npython cli.py --temperature 25 --from celsius --to fahrenheit\\n# Output: 25 celsius is equal to 77.0 fahrenheit.\\n```\\n\\n## Testing\\n\\nRun tests using pytest:\\n\\n```bash\\npytest test_converters.py test_cli.py\\n```\\n\\n## Limitations\\n\\n- This version only supports conversions between Celsius, Fahrenheit, and Kelvin for the following specific pairs:\\n  - Celsius → Fahrenheit\\n  - Fahrenheit → Celsius\\n  - Celsius → Kelvin\\n- Other conversions (e.g., Fahrenheit → Kelvin) are not implemented.\\n- The CLI tool explicitly lists unsupported conversions with a message like:\\n  `\"Conversion from {args.from} to {args.to} is not supported\"`'\n\n**Issues Identified:**\n1. **Incomplete Conversion Support**  \n   The tool only supports three specific conversions:  \n   - Celsius → Fahrenheit  \n   - Fahrenheit → Celsius  \n   - Celsius → Kelvin  \n   It does **not** support conversions like:  \n   - Fahrenheit → Kelvin  \n   - Kelvin → Celsius  \n   - Kelvin → Fahrenheit  \n   These are valid use cases, and the code currently lacks the logic to handle them. The `converters.py` file does not provide functions for these conversions, but the tool should still inform users about this limitation.\n\n2. **Error Message Ambiguity**  \n   The error message `\"Conversion from {args.from} to {args.to} is not supported\"` is correct but could be improved by explicitly listing supported conversions (e.g., \"Supported conversions: Celsius→Fahrenheit, Fahrenheit→Celsius, Celsius→Kelvin\"). This would help users avoid confusion when encountering unsupported conversions."},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/nathangreen/Development/eddi-lab/llm-orc/scratch/spike-sigma-premature-finish/frontier_judge/ws_3/converters.py","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"scratch/spike-sigma-premature-finish/frontier_judge/ws_3/converters.py","time":{"start":1781051178584,"end":1781051178598}},"id":"prt_eaeec3e48001KWe7NKlVAkwH7s","sessionID":"ses_1511b64a7ffevvFJkOHaY5EHeu","messageID":"msg_eaee49bce001oX3LQU5A7arE8d"}}
